WEBVTT

00:06.652 --> 00:08.486
<i>(Man whistling)</i>

00:08.575 --> 00:11.943
Caleb: ♪ I took her to a tavern ♪

00:11.978 --> 00:14.879
♪ And treated her with wine ♪

00:14.915 --> 00:17.649
♪ Little did I think that she was one ♪

00:17.684 --> 00:20.005
♪ Of the rakish kind ♪

00:20.040 --> 00:22.887
♪ I handled her, I dandled her ♪

00:22.923 --> 00:26.524
♪ And much to my surprise ♪

00:26.560 --> 00:29.880
♪ Turns out she was a fire ship ♪

00:29.905 --> 00:32.604
♪ Rigged up in a disguise ♪

00:33.775 --> 00:37.110
♪ And in the morning she was gone ♪

00:37.145 --> 00:39.846
♪ My money was gone, too ♪

00:39.881 --> 00:43.416
♪ My clothes she'd hocked,
my watch she stole ♪

00:43.452 --> 00:46.086
♪ My seabag bid adieu ♪

00:46.121 --> 00:49.089
Man: <i>♪ But she left behind a souvenir ♪</i>

00:49.124 --> 00:51.791
♪ I'll have you all to know ♪

00:51.827 --> 00:55.895
Both: ♪ And in nine
days, to my surprise ♪

00:55.931 --> 01:00.333
♪ There was fire down below. ♪

01:02.170 --> 01:03.970
(laughing)

01:04.006 --> 01:07.073
- Robby Beddows.
- Brewster, you son of a fish town whore.

01:07.109 --> 01:10.110
I'm sure you've harpooned
more than one tainted target.

01:10.145 --> 01:12.946
Now, now, Robby. Don't speak
of your mother like that.

01:12.981 --> 01:15.415
- It's poor manners.
- (knife clinks)

01:20.522 --> 01:23.423
So, what's your haul?

01:23.458 --> 01:25.558
(Sighs) The mother lode.

01:25.594 --> 01:27.738
Twenty brace of ham hocks.

01:29.831 --> 01:31.998
- A man could retire on that.
- Aye.

01:33.502 --> 01:35.702
It's a shame you have to
come all this way for mine.

01:35.737 --> 01:36.970
I'll double your fee if you tell me

01:37.005 --> 01:38.304
who you work with on the Tory side.

01:38.340 --> 01:41.141
Ah, not a chance, Rob. Not a chance.

01:41.176 --> 01:43.754
You want a piece of the London
trade, you go through me.

01:44.780 --> 01:48.882
I tell you, Caleb, London trade
ain't what it used to be.

01:48.917 --> 01:51.017
Privateer's raiding loads on both sides,

01:51.053 --> 01:55.121
others moving on to kidnapping...
or so I hear.

01:55.157 --> 01:58.258
Like there ain't no honor
among thieves anymore. Hmm?

01:58.293 --> 02:00.560
(Chuckles)

02:00.595 --> 02:01.795
Do you mind if I sample the wares?

02:05.600 --> 02:07.133
As long as you don't drain my profits.

02:07.169 --> 02:08.901
- Oh.
- <i>(twig snaps)</i>

02:09.871 --> 02:11.538
- (groans)
- (gunshot)

02:15.377 --> 02:18.178
- I told you to keep him distracted.
- (Caleb coughing)

02:18.213 --> 02:19.746
Where's my brother?

